doctype html
html
    head
        title= title
        script(language="JavaScript" type="text/javascript" src='/js/jquery-2.1.1.min.js')
        script(language="JavaScript" type="text/javascript" src='/js/bootstrap.min.js')
        link(rel='stylesheet' href='/css/ah-styles.min.css')
        link(rel='stylesheet' href='/css/bootstrap.min.css')
        link(rel='stylesheet' href='/css/ah-tm.howto.css')
    body
        div(style="border-top: 2px solid rgb(255, 195, 15);" class="user-home-wrap")
        div.clearfix(id='main')
            div.pt-r
                div(id="container")
                    //div.grid_20.LoginPage
                    div.howto-page
                        img(src="/images/login_page_logo.png" alt="Aerohive" class="ah-logo")
                        div.ah-growing-hives(style="position: fixed; top: 0px; right: 10%;")

                        div.howto-box(style="width: 80%")
                            div
                                h1(style="text-align: center; margin-top: 10px;") Quick Start Guide
                                span.
                                    This Quick Start Guide will help you to find the needed information to get access
                                    to the Presence Analytics dashboard.
                                h4
                                    span= '1. Log in to your '
                                    a(href="http://cloud.aerohive.com" targer="_blank") HiveManager NG
                                    span= ' account'
                                h4
                                    span 2. Get your Datacenter address
                                span.
                                    Look at the address bar from your web browser.
                                    The URL will indicate you on which datacenter your HiveManager NG account is deployed.
                                div(style="width:100%")
                                    img(src="/images/howto/howto_2.png" style="width: 400px")
                                br
                                span Currenty, the possible choices are:
                                ul(style="list-style: inside none disc; padding-left: 30px;")
                                    for apiServer in apiServers
                                        li= apiServer
                                h4
                                    span 3. Get your Owner ID
                                span On your HiveManager NG interface, click on the
                                b=' "User" '
                                span icon on the top right of the interface, then click on
                                b=' "About" '
                                img(src="/images/howto/howto_3.png" style="width: 400px;")
                                span On the popup, you will find the
                                b=' OwnerID '
                                span under the name
                                b=' VHM-ID :'
                                img(src="/images/howto/howto_3.1.png" style="width: 400px;")
                                h4
                                    span 4. Generate an
                                    b=' Access Token '
                                    span for this Web APP
                                span On your HiveManager NG interface, click on the
                                b=' "Configuration" '
                                span icon on the top right, then click on
                                b=' API Token Management '
                                span and to finish click on the
                                b=' + '
                                img(src="/images/howto/howto_4.png" style="width: 800px;")
                                span On the popup window, enter the
                                b=' Client ID '
                                b(style="color: rgb(54, 148, 209)")= clientID
                                span=' to generate a new '
                                b AccessToken 
                                h4
                                    span 5. Once you have all the information, go back to the
                                    a(href='/')=' Login Page '
                                    span and have fun!
                                span.error.
                                    Be sure to have already configured some location on your HiveManager NG account before using this Web APP!

